<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Box Model Demo</title>
    <style>
        /* Default styles */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        
        /* Box model demonstration */
        .box {
            width: 200px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        
        /* Border-box model */
        .border-box {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            width: 200px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        
        /* Content-box model */
        .content-box {
            box-sizing: content-box;
            width: 200px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        
        /* Padding and margin examples */
        .padding-example {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #ccc;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        
        .margin-example {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #ccc;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        
        .border-example {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: #ccc;
            border: 10px solid #ccc;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>CSS Box Model Demo</h1>
    <p>Here are some examples of how padding, border, and margin affect different elements:</p>
    <div class="box">
        <p>This is a box with padding, border, and margin.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Switching to border-box model:</p>
    <div class="border-box">
        <p>This is a box with padding, border, and margin in border-box model.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Switching to content-box model:</p>
    <div class="content-box">
        <p>This is a box with padding, border, and margin in content-box model.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Padding examples:</p>
    <div class="padding-example">
        <p>This is a box with padding only.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Margin examples:</p>
    <div class="margin-example">
        <p>This is a box with margin only.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Border examples:</p>
    <div class="border-example">
        <p>This is a box with a border only.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
